item.dc:creator: @the_soul The Soul
item.description:
@the_soul wrote:

[quote=“relmitos, post:8, topic:320750”]As Soul said, the case is outside a switch statement.

switch(case number){[/quote]

It should be:

switch(var) {

You can switch any data type, but I wouldn’t recommend switching a boolean (it’d be pointless). If I remember correctly, you’ll be able to switch Strings in the next JDK update (don’t quote me on it).

item.title: Quick question
item.dc:creator: @relmitos relmitos
item.description:
@relmitos wrote:

As Soul said, the case is outside a switch statement.

switch(case number){
case 1:
break;
case 2:
break;
default:
break;
}

When a case is outside a switch, this error will occur:

clickingMost.java:65: orphaned case case 73172: ^

Hopefully this will clear things up for you:

switch(example){
case 1: //this case is inside a switch.
break; //Similiar to a closing bracket “}”
}//end of the switch statement
case 73172: //this case is outside the switch. Thus orphaned.
break;
